# Generated harness build artifacts. These are regenerated from the KiCad
# schematics by CI (extract_connectors.py + wirelab build) on every push to
# main, so their committed content is a moving target: two branches will
# almost always have different bytes and would otherwise conflict on merge.
#
# Mark them with the built-in "ours" merge strategy so a merge/rebase never
# produces conflict markers in them -- it just keeps one side. The next CI
# run on main regenerates the canonical version regardless, so whichever side
# git keeps is only transient. This keeps the diagram viewable in the repo
# without letting it block merges.
#
# NOTE: the "ours" driver must also be registered in git config. This repo's
# CI and a one-time local setup do that via:
#     git config merge.ours.driver true
# (contributors who merge locally should run that once; see harness/README.md)
harness/output/car.svg          merge=ours
harness/generated/*.yaml        merge=ours
